title: ESA troubleshooting JUICE radar antenna
summary: A radar antenna on a European mission to Jupiter has yet to fully deploy after launch, although project officials say they still have plenty of options to fix the problem.

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy launches first ViaSat-3 satellite
summary: SpaceX launched the Americas-focused ViaSat-3 broadband satellite on a Falcon Heavy rocket April 30 following delays partly caused by severe weather that included lightning and tornado warnings.

summary: After a string of weather delays and an abort in the final minute of the countdown, SpaceX is targeting to launch the...

title: Spaceport Cornwall Opens A New Satellite Center
summary: New satellite center opens at Spaceport Cornwell.

title: ViaSat-3 Americas launches on expendable Falcon Heavy
summary: Falcon Heavy’s second launch 2023 will try again on Sunday, with liftoff with the ViaSat-3 Americas satellite as the main payload, plus the much smaller Arcturus and G-Space 1 rideshare satellites.

title: Elon Musk Gives Update on Failed Starship Launch, Expected To Spend $2B This Year
summary: On Saturday evening, SpaceX CEO Elon Musk took to Twitter to give an update on the Starship Flight Test which took place on April 20th, 2023, and to provide insight into the future of the program.

title: Musk predicts next Starship launch in a “couple months”
summary: SpaceX Chief Executive Elon Musk said the first integrated test flight of his company's Starship vehicle met his expectations despite a cascading series of engine failures and other malfunctions that eventually caused the rocket to lose control.

title: SpaceX to spend about $2 billion on Starship this year, as Elon Musk pushes to reach orbit
summary: Elon Musk expects SpaceX to spend about $2 billion on its Starship rocket development this year, as the company pushes to build on its first launch earlier this month.

title: What’s next for SpaceX’s Starship after a dramatic first launch
summary: The dust has settled in Texas, but the work to clean up after the world’s most powerful rocket and get the next one flying in a matter of months is already underway.

title: SpaceX launches second pair of O3b mPower satellites
summary: SpaceX launched a second pair of O3b mPower satellites April 28 for SES, which is now just one launch away from bringing its next-generation broadband constellation in medium Earth orbit online.
